      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Govt. House ¶ Fiji ¶ Dear Baron Von Mueller. ¶  ¶ Thanks for your very welcome note ¶ Letter not found. ¶  ¶ and the seed accompanying it. ¶  ¶ The latter were planted at once ¶  ¶ and some of them — ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.00.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Thurston</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M76, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS letter head: 'ESSE QUAM VIDERI' [To be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>rather than to seem].</p>
               </note>Govt. House</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Fiji</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron Von Mueller.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thanks for your very welcome note<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and the seed accompanying it.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The latter were planted at once<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and some of them — notably the interesting, and to me new, Madagascar ground nut — have already germinated &amp; are well above ground</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall not fail to send you a photo of the Musa you require. In a former note<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Thurston to M, 2 April 1886, which provides the basis for accepting the tentative dating of the present letter to later in 1886, Thurston seeming to imply that M had not yet responded to the earlier note.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I mentioned [that] a disease had attacked this family of plants — principally M. cavendishii but my M. uranoscopa<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">M. uranoscopus</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have also suffered.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will also send you photos of the male and female Cycad you so kindly described for me many years ago<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Thurston to M, 2 October 1882.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Based on Thurston's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>specimens,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M provided<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in B82.08.02 (republished as B83.07.02)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a more complete description of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Cycas seemanii</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>than that given by Braun (1876a), p. 114 when he named it.</p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am applying photography to my very humble botanical pursuit and find it most useful. The process I adopt is the "Bromide" which is comparatively permanent.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With kind regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very faithfully yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John B. Thurston.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Musa<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Cavendishii</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Musa<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>uranoscopa</p>
         </div>
